@startuml
title LSM hooks — DAC first, then mandatory access control

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Process" as p
rectangle "System call\n(open, exec, socket, ...)" as sc
rectangle "Standard DAC check\n(POSIX rwx / owner / capabilities)" as dac
rectangle "LSM hook\nplaced on the kernel function" as hook

package "Active security module(s)" {
  rectangle "MAC modules (one major)\nSELinux | AppArmor | SMACK | TOMOYO" as mac
  rectangle "Targeted modules (stackable)\nYama | LoadPin | SafeSetID | Lockdown" as minor
}

rectangle "Access granted\n(only if DAC AND every module allow)" as grant
rectangle "Access denied" as deny

p --> sc
sc --> dac
dac --> deny : DAC says no
dac --> hook : DAC says yes
hook --> mac
hook --> minor
mac --> deny : policy denies
minor --> deny : module denies
mac --> grant : policy allows
minor --> grant : module allows

note bottom of mac
  MAC decision does not depend on the
  object owner: even root is bound by
  the policy. This is the DAC->MAC shift.
end note
@enduml
